recipe /ˈrɛsɪpɪ/

(recipes) 

1. N-COUNT A recipe is a list of ingredients and a set of instructions that tell you how to cook something. 食谱 

例： ...a traditional recipe for buttermilk biscuits. …一个酪乳饼干的传统烹饪法。 

2. N-SING If you say that something is a recipe for a particular situation, you mean that it is likely to result in that situation. 方法 

例： Large-scale inflation is a recipe for disaster. 大规模的通货膨胀有可能导致灾难。

